window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Back in print in an all-new edition is the engaging and illuminating chronicle of the life of the \"Queen of Mystery\". Fans of Hercule Poirot and Miss Marple and readers of John Curran’s fascinating biographies <i>Agatha Christie’s Secret Notebooks</i> and <i>Murder in the Making</i> will be spellbound by the compelling, authoritative account of one of the world’s most influential and fascinating novelists, told in her own words and inimitable style - and here in her own voice. These audio excerpts were dictated by Agatha Christie herself.&nbsp;</p> <p>The <i>New York Times Book Review</i> called Christie’s autobiography a \"joyful adventure,\" saying, \"she brings the sense of wonder... to her extraordinary career.\"</p> <p><b>Please note: This is a historical recording, and the audio quality is reflective of the time in which it was recorded.</b></p>"; 
